# MVP Scope Discipline

- Preserve the core promise: proactive earthquake preparedness before disaster time.
- Keep v1 focused on score engine, weekly tasks, emergency bag, family mode, offline guide, SOS, and notifications.
- Explicitly defer out-of-scope items (e.g., early warning, building analysis, DASK integration, web app, AI chatbot).
- When proposing features, label each item as `MVP` or `v2+`.
- Avoid adding dependencies or integrations not justified by current MVP success metrics.

# Writing Guidance

- Use concise decisions with rationale and trade-offs.
- Prefer measurable language (targets, limits, timing) over vague statements.
- When a scope change is suggested, include impact on timeline and complexity.
